Shaders:
- OpenGL Shading Language GLSL
___

- Vertex Shaders
- Fragment Shaders
___

Vertex shaders:
- Attribute: Per vertex information (position, color, etc)
- Uniform: Global variables that every vertex will use
- out / in: passed from one shader to the other
___

Very much like c languge
- int,ivec2, ivec3, ivec4
- float, vec2, vec3, vec4
- mat2, mat3, mat4
- bool, bvec2, bvec3, bvec4
- sampler for accessing texture
- vector components accessed through [index] notation, .rgba, .xyzw or .stpq
- parallel SIMD operations
- Vector component Swizzling (rearranged)
- discard (not process a pixel)
